== root cause assessment ==
Most likely: Pentagon desktop app native trigger poller desynced/not polling triggers.
Evidence: runner intentionally stopped the bridge, so bridge daemon state cannot explain native trigger pickup; Pentagon.app process was present, Maya agent config remained canonical, trigger row existed for Maya and stayed claimed_at=null completed_at=null for the full 40-minute watch, while the runner restored bridge only after failure. This isolates failure to the native app/poller trigger-claim path rather than missing trigger creation, agent config drift, or bridge death.
hypothesis=a: bridge daemon died silently -> unlikely for native run; bridge was intentionally stopped and later restored, and native trigger should be claimed by Pentagon.app.
hypothesis=b: Pentagon desktop app desynced / not polling triggers -> most likely.
hypothesis=c: trigger-table state machine stuck -> possible secondary, but new trigger row was ordinary pending state with null claimed/completed.
hypothesis=d: Maya config drifted -> check agent row above; expected canonical config.
